measure.CatchLine: Allows counties to designate certain rural lands for rural housing development that are not subject to statewide land use planning laws.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: This Act lets counties zone land for rural housing development. (Flesch Readability Score: 61.3). 
	Allows counties to designate certain rural lands for rural housing development that are not subject to statewide land use planning laws. Exempts the lands from repayment of additional property taxes based on disqualification from special assessment.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to rural housing development; creating new provisions; and amending ORS 308A.706.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
